"content": "# Jarvis 2.9 - Minimal Meta-Engine\n\n## Current Build: Distributed Orchestration (ORCH) - Cluster Computing (v2.9)\n\n### Structure\n- core/framework/output.py - Basic I/O\n- core/engine/interpreter.py - SqVGr interpreter\n- core/engine/jit.py - Just-In-Time compiler\n- core/orchestrator/engine.py - Local orchestrator\n- core/orchestrator/distributed.py - Distributed task manager\n- core/orchestrator/delegator.py - Task delegation to nodes\n- core/daemon/listener.py - Daemon with distributed mode\n- core/network/discovery.py - Node discovery (multicast)\n- core/network/client.py - Memory sync client\n- core/network/server.py - HTTP server with /execute endpoint\n- core/metacontrol/* - Memory, vectorizer, optimizer, evolve\n- core/physics/* - Sensors and actuators\n- core/life/* - Autonomy, scheduler, goals\n- core/compiler/* - Bytecode, optimization, cache\n\n### New in v2.9\n- Node discovery via multicast (port 5005)\n- Remote execution endpoint (/execute)\n- Task delegation and result collection\n- Split tasks into subtasks for parallel execution\n- Distributed mode CLI flag (--distributed)\n- Node failure detection and task redistribution\n- Integration with scheduler for distributed tasks\n\n### Run\n\nServer (memory + execution):\nbash\npython run_server.py\n\n\nClient 1:\nbash\npython run_daemon.py --sync --autonomous --distributed\n\n\nClient 2 (another machine):\nbash\npython run_daemon.py --sync --distributed\n\n\nTest discovery:\nbash\npython run_discovery.py\n\n\n### Distributed Commands\n- dist:сколько времени - execute on remote node\n- dist:запиши в файл test.txt привет - remote file write\n- Commands with dist: prefix use distributed execution\n\n### Architecture\n- Multicast for node discovery (auto-configuration)\n- HTTP for task execution\n- Automatic failover\n- Load balancing (simple round-robin)\n- Task splitting for parallel processing"
